## Authenticate Your Requests
Most endpoints in EcommerceAPI require authentication using your API key. You can include your API key as a query parameter in the URL or use the Authorization header with the value Bearer YOUR_API_KEY.

## Test the API
Before integrating EcommerceAPI into your application, we recommend testing it using tools like Postman or cURL. This allows you to familiarize yourself with the API's functionality and ensure it meets your requirements.

## Start Integrating
Once you're comfortable with the API, you can start integrating it into your application. Whether you're retrieving product information, processing orders, or managing customer data, our API provides the flexibility and scalability you need.

## Support
If you have any questions or need assistance, our dedicated support team is here to help. You can reach us via email at support@ecommerceapi.com.

## Versioning
This documentation is for version 1.0 of EcommerceAPI. We may release updates and improvements in the future, so be sure to check back regularly for the latest information.

